    {
      "title": "The Absolute Object (المفعول المطلق)",
      "titleArabic": "المفعول المطلق",
      "content": [
        "The maf'ūl muṭlaq (absolute object) is a maṣdar (verbal noun) from the same root as the verb, used to emphasize the action, indicate its number, or specify its type."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Used for emphasis: ضَرَبْتُهُ ضَرْبًا (I hit him a hitting)",
        "Indicates number: ضَرَبْتُهُ ضَرْبَتَيْنِ (I hit him two hittings)",
        "Specifies type: ضَرَبْتُهُ ضَرْبًا شَدِيدًا (I hit him a severe hitting)",
        "Can be replaced by words indicating 'all' or 'some'"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "فَهِمْتُهُ فَهْمًا كَامِلًا", "english": "I understood it completely" },
        { "arabic": "أَحَبَّتْهُ حُبًّا كَثِيرًا", "english": "She loved him greatly" },
        { "arabic": "شَكَرْتُهُ شُكْرًا جَزِيلًا", "english": "I thanked him greatly" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Words Deputizing for Maṣdar",
      "titleArabic": "النائب عن المصدر",
      "content": [
        "Certain words can substitute for the maṣdar in the absolute object construction. These include words indicating all, some, kind, or instrument."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "كُلّ (all): ضَرَبْتُهُ كُلَّ الضَّرْبِ",
        "بَعْض (some): ضَرَبْتُهُ بَعْضَ الضَّرْبِ",
        "Demonstratives: ضَرَبْتُهُ ذَلِكَ الضَّرْبَ",
        "Numbers: ضَرَبْتُهُ ثَلَاثَ ضَرَبَاتٍ"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "ضَرَبْتُهُ كُلَّ الضَّرْبِ", "english": "I hit him with all hitting" },
        { "arabic": "جَلَسَ جُلُوسًا طَوِيلًا", "english": "He sat a long sitting" }
      ]
    }
  ],
